description: For three years the only thing Shy Stevens could live for was one thing: revenge. After intensive training and small guerrilla attacks she finally got her chance to face the man who took her innocence, tried to have her killed, and left her with child. For so long Shy's goal was worth anything, including her life, but after killing Jeno Jacobs and nearly dying herself she discovered a new passion- the beauty of life and family. This comic is dedicated to the strong women out there willing to do whatever it takes to ensure the survival of their loved ones. Includes ChiSai: Karma part 3.
name: Exclusive Pin-Up Comic

description: Revenge. The one word that drives 18-year-old Shy Stevens. After being brutally raped, beaten, and left for dead, Shy picks up the pieces and undergoes two years of stict and brutal training. Armed with these deadly abilities and a special woven bulletproof uniform she resurfaces to put her life on the line for one shot at fulfilling her life's mission. Features a preview of ChiSai: Duality!

ChiSai chronicles the life of young Shy Stevens, an 18 year girl whose life was torn apart in every way imaginable, yet she dedicates herself to crawling from the wreckage and settling the score. But once she's rebuilt her life and goes about getting revenge on her tormentors, she faces risking her new life and family to settle her old scores. Features a further look at the upcoming ChiSai: Duality series and a sneak peek at ChiSai: Conception!

Darwyn Cooke (DC: THE NEW FRONTIER) teams with REBIRTH writer Geoff Johns for the lead story of an extra-sized special! Hal Jordan relives some of the most meaningful flights in his life, joined by an unexpected partner. Rounding out the issue are the prelude to GREEN LANTERN: REBIRTH (by Johns, Van Sciver and Rollins), previously found only in the pages of Wizard, plus, profiles of Hal Jordan, his enemies, allies and more!
name: Flight & The Day Before

volume.name: Green Lantern Secret Files and Origins 2005

description: You're flying on the back of giant, birdlike reptile, floating cloudlike high above a surreal landscape. Then, you're in an ordinary automobile, taking an obscure back-road detour through a land replete with eerie stone monoliths, clashing mythic armies, and curious giants who loom like lonely sentinels over sprawling, multi-hued otherworldly vistas. You've stepped into the haunting dreams of Moebius. Dark Horse Comics is proud to present Arzach, collecting the dreamlike images and groundbreaking visual storytelling techniques of Jean Giraud (Moebius). This is Moebius' most fascinating science-fantasy material to date, including his innovative wordless "pantomime" work, and his now legendary hero, Arzach. Arzach also includes a tribute to horror legend H. P. Lovecraft and a surreal Moebius autobiographical comic strip. No bookshelf of fine graphic literature is complete without Arzach.
name: Arzach

description:
1. "Autograph Please!" reprinted from Superman #48.
  2. "The Juvenile Delinquents from Space!" reprinted from Action Comics #315-#316.
  3. Two page centerfold of Superman.
  4. "DC Cover Gallery" 1/3 page featuring the covers of Superman #40 and Action Comics #315.
  5. "Super-Game" contains an image and scrambled name of 9 characters from Superman's supporting cast by Bob Rozakis.
  6. "The Mxyztplk - Susie Alliance!" reprinted from Superman #40.
  7. "How to Draw the Superman Family" two pages featuring Superman, Superbaby, Krypto and Mr. Mxyztplk by Curt Swan.
  8. "Superman's Day of Doom!" reprinted from Superman #157.
  9. "Superman's Young Friends on Film" one page on the back cover featuring 6 b/w photos of George Reeves with children by Allan Asherman.
  10. "Table-Top Diorama" back cover featuring a Superman cutout diorama.

Notes:

  • A 64-page no ads all-reprint issue.
  • Issue number designated as C-38.
name: Superman

description: Peek into the mind of a great cartoonist with this director's take, adapting a favorite episode of Dexter's Laboratory! A comet approaches Earth--can Dexter save the day with science, or will he have to team up with...Mandark? The earth is doomed! It's DEXTER the Genndy way in "Let's Save the World, You Jerk!"
A boy and his robot usually means fun, right? Not when it's Robo-Dexter! Also, Dexter and Dee-Dee go head to head in a hamster race, in "Habi-Travails."
To defeat Dexter, Mandark decides to impersonate the person closest to him...his mom! Will Dexter detect the imposter in time?
name: Meanwhile...

description: Will Dexter be betrayed by the person who is closest to him? Will Mandark finally learn the secrets of Dexter's lab? Find out in "Momdark."
name: Momdark!

description: Dexter's got the chicken pox. He must not scratch. He...must...not...scratch. And Dee-Dee is his only hope! Plus, Dexter's scheme to slow time so he has more time in the day has unexpected consequences.
name: Chicken Scratch; Wait A Minute

description: It's Dexter of the Apes as a trip to the zoo finds Dexter living among the monkeys in "Beast Master." Then, in "Bubble Boy," a bubble-blowing contest pits Dexter and Dee-Dee against each other yet again.
name: Beast Master; Bubble Boy

description: A giant Dee-Dee roams the world! Dexter's only hope is to shrink her back to normal size using his shrinking gun...if only his aim wasn't so bad!
name: Dee-Dee-Fo-Fum

description: She's short, she wears thick horn-rimmed glasses, a lab coat and rubber gloves. Her name is Doreen, and she's the ideal girl for Dexter! But will their scientific rivalry tear their love apart? Find out in "Perfect Chemistry."

When Dexter creates a super-dense blue donut to foil Dee-Dee's breakfast greed, he creates a fantastic "blue hole" which begins to suck in everything blue in the world ‹ from the ocean to Dee-Dee's eyes (eeeew)! Can Dexter's science save the world from his own creation?

When Dexter's very last pair of precious gloves are destroyed in a lab accident he sets his eyes on the nearest replacement: Mom's rubber gloves! Plus, Dexter hits on the ultimate solution to the Dee-Dee problem: clone a smarter Dee-Dee! But is a brighter Dee-Dee really such a smart idea?
name: No Gloves, No Love

description: For years, Dexter's dumped his failed experiments down the kitchen sink ‹ but now they've come back to haunt him in "Protoplasm Man!" Plus, Dexter pits his brainpower against an unwanted tattoo in "Under Dexter's Skin."
name: Protoplasm Man!; Under Dexter's Skin

description: Dexter's a genius, but he can't tell a good joke. Can science give him a funny bone? Plus, only Dee-Dee can stop the lab from blowing up in "Forget Me Not!"

It's no secret that Dexter is always the teacher's pet...but now he's the star entry in the annual Teacher's Pet Show! It's the weirdest, wildest Dexter yarn yet as he throws all his genius into winning a blue ribbon for brown-nosing! Featuring the debut of new cover artist Bill Wray!
name: Teacher's Pet

description: When Dee-Dee needs a new goldfish, Dexter gets "Totally Tanked" trying to help; plus, Dexter sets out to create the perfect winter weapon in "The Abdominable Snowball!"
name: Totally Tanked; The Abominable Snowball
